cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically on improving the efficiency of convolutional networks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel learning algorithm that combines supervised and reinforcement learning, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the formulation of the dynamic skipping problem in the context of sequential decision making, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a gating network to selectively skip convolutional blocks also involves neural networks, which is relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of SkipNet on benchmark datasets, which is related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
